onclusions: As we consider longer period exoplanets the need for exploring\nsingle transit detections increases. For periods $\\gtrsim45$ days the number of\nsingle transit detections outnumber multitransits by a factor of 3 (82$\\pm$18\nand 25$\\pm$7 respectively) a factor which only grows as longer period\ndetections are considered. Therefore, it is worth expending the extra effort\nrequired to follow-up these more challenging, but potentially very rewarding,\ndiscoveries. Additionally, we conclude that a large fraction of these targets\ncan be theoretically observed from just a single ground-based site.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Sep 2018 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-21"}
