rein to determine the most probable orbital periods will be\nimportant for long-period planets detected by the Transiting Exoplanet Survey\nSatellite, where similar period ambiguities will frequently arise due to the\ntelescope's survey strategy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Sep 2018 18:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Jun 2019 17:16:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-27"}
