ancies are often found to be less than 5\nK throughout the atmosphere. ALMA's excellent sensitivity in the lower\nstratosphere (60-300 km) provides a highly complementary dataset to\ncontemporary CIRS and radio science observations. The demonstrated utility of\nCO emission lines in the submillimeter as a tracer of Titan's atmospheric\ntemperature lays the groundwork for future studies of other molecular species,\nas temperature profiles are found to consistently vary with latitude in all\nthree years by up to 15 K.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Sep 2018 07:30:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-01"}
